The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | EB-Bagan may play on April 2
                                                                                                                       7                                      EB-Bagan may play on April 2
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The I-League sub-committee has proposed a provisional date of April 2 for the return leg derby between East Bengal and Mohun Bagan.         
	In a meeting of the sub-committee, in New Delhi, it was decided that the I-League will resume on January 7. The provisional fixture will be handed over to the I-League clubs to seek their opinion.         
	According to the fixture, Chirag United are likely to take on East Bengal on January 7.         
	However, the committee has decided that the I-League teams that will bow out of the Federation Cup (December 21-January 3) at the group league stages will start their I-League proceedings earlier.         
	The I-League matches will again be postponed from February 16 to 26 when the AFC Challenge Cup will be held. A camp will be held from February 2-15.         
	The AIFF has already done a review of all the I-League clubs. We will be sending a report of the review to all the clubs. Also, we will have another meeting in the second week of January (January 14, tentatively) to discuss about the players who will be taken under the AIFF payrolls from June, 2010 till 2011 Asian Cup in Doha.         
	The modalities will also be discussed in the same meeting, informed IFA secretary and committee member Utpal Ganguli.         
	Other Decisions         
	 The AIFF has appointed B.K. Roka, a former IPS officer and working president of Sikkim Football Association, as their independent security officer He has also done an AFC security course.         
	 The AIFF has asked the AFC to appoint an independent observer who will audit the licensing of the I-League clubs.                                                                                                                     
